# Commit in small, scoped commits

This is a monorepo with several independent workstreams (`backend/`,
`admin/`, `facility-portal/`, the Flutter app in `lib/` + `android/` +
`ios/`, `assets/`, `supabase/`). Do NOT batch unrelated changes into one
giant commit.

## Rules

- **One workstream/concern per commit.** Group by area and intent, e.g.:
  - backend import pipeline / services / routes
  - facility-portal feature
  - admin portal feature
  - Flutter app feature
  - assets / branding
  - supabase migrations
- **Commit incrementally** as each logical unit is done, rather than letting
  changes pile up. Stage only the relevant paths (`git add <paths>`), not
  `git add -A`, unless the whole change truly is one concern.
- **Only commit when the user asks.** Never auto-commit.
- Keep generated build artifacts (e.g. `*.tsbuildinfo`) out of commits when
  practical.

## Windows / PowerShell mechanics

The shell is PowerShell. `&&` and heredocs (`$(cat <<'EOF')`) do NOT work.

- Run git steps as separate commands or chain with `;`.
- For multi-line messages, write the message to a temp file and use
  `git commit -F <file>`.
- This repo has no committed git identity. Commit with a per-command
  override (do NOT modify git config):

```bash
git -c user.name="shepherd-chikomo" -c user.email="shepherd-chikomo@users.noreply.github.com" commit -F <msgfile>
```

## Message style

Imperative, sentence case, ends with a period; optional bullet body
describing the "why". Match existing history.
